snippet.textDisplay:
I think it's funny that people these days think wires on headphones were somehow never a problem. I got mad when Apple cut the cord so to speak with eliminating the headphone jack. Now that I look back on it, I realize they were not creating a problem to later solve it - they were solving an issue I already had forgotten about.

WIRED FUCKING HEADPHONES ARE A PAIN IN THE ASS.

Look they sound better. There is far more variety. However wires get in the way of movement. They get snagged on things. They tether you to a device. They get ripped out. They get ruined. They fray and shit.

I use my bose qc35ii's ALL THE TIME and I love the freedom of movement more than I love the sound quality I miss from my "good" "audiophile" headphones. Sure side by side they are not as high quality but I forget about it during work when I can walk around, take a shit, take calls, watch a show, chill at home etc etc --- all without getting stuck on wires.

Eventually wireless sound will rival that of wired sound. I'm looking forward to it!

LOVE my AirPods (still on original)..
Though what are peeps thoughts on EMF? It does seem concerning with wireless buds.

Airpods SAR rating is 0.466 w/kg
iPhone 11 SAR rating is 1.41 w/kg
Apple Watch S5 cellular is 0.59 w/kg; 0.34 on wrist
(Non cellular is 0.16 w/kg; 0.08 on wrist)

Just me or do Airpods seem a bit high powered?
Apparently a few Bluetooth buds are just as bad. I know it’s “non-ionising” and lower power Bluetooth radios, but the fact people (myself included) are wearing these for hours a day instead of just for a call, right in/on the head, has made me rethink my level of usage.

I still love them though.. 🧐
